From 9941a6bfbd59a761b18834a6732cf8406570036f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yong Zhao <Yong.Zhao@amd.com>
Date: Sat, 21 Sep 2019 20:02:57 -0400
Subject: drm/amdkfd: Delete useless SDMA register setting on non HWS path
Git-commit: 9941a6bfbd59a761b18834a6732cf8406570036f
Patch-mainline: v5.5-rc1
References: bsc#1152489

HW folks have confirm that we should not touch RESUME_CTX of
SDMA*_GFX_CONTEXT_CNTL when manipulating RLC queues.

Signed-off-by: Yong Zhao <Yong.Zhao@amd.com>
Reviewed-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Acked-by: Thomas Zimmermann <tzimmermann@suse.de>
---
